article.headline: Pennsylvania 87, Columbia 55
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Zoller scored 21 points and Ibrahim Jaaber added 18 as Penn used two huge scoring bursts to rout Columbia 87-55 Saturday night. Zoller connected on 8-of-9 shots, including 2-of-2 from 3-point range, while Jaaber was 7-for-10 and 4-of-6 from behind the arc for the Quakers (8-5, 2-0 Ivy League). Justin Armstrong had 16 points for the Lions (7-8, 0-2), which lost to Penn for the eighth straight time. With the score tied 16-16 with 11:07 left in the first half, Jaaber and Zoller each hit 3-pointers to ignite a 21-6 run, and the Quakers led 37-22 at the break. Penn started the second half with a 16-0 spurt, including two 3-point shots by Eric Osmundson, to build a 53-22 lead. Columbia never got closer than 27 points the rest of the way. It was the Quakers' second lopsided win in two nights, following an 84-44 victory over Cornell on Friday night.
